overview: "The user initiated a review of their recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application, providing a detailed Statement of Work and
  questionnaire content. The assistant performed a comprehensive code review,
  identifying several areas where the current implementation deviated from or
  lacked features specified in the requirements. A structured plan was then
  presented, prioritizing the identified gaps. The assistant then began
  implementing the first high-priority item: integrating a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness interference. This involved updating data types, validation
  schemas, the UI component for the questionnaire section, and the report
  generation logic to display a critical safety warning for severe tiredness
  levels. This ensures the application accurately captures and communicates
  potential safety risks related to a user's sleep health."
